---
id: org.dxos.plugin.inbox
name: InboxPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

Unified inbox plugin for `DXOS` Composer — email, calendar, and contacts in one place, synced from Google and surfaced alongside workspace content.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |

## Types

```mdl
type MessageState
  literals: none | archived | deleted | spam
```

```mdl
type Filter
  fields:
    name: string
    filter: string              # query expression
```

```mdl
type Mailbox
  fields:
    name?: string
    feed: Ref<Feed>             # append-only Message stream
    labels?: Map<string, string>
    filters: Filter[]
    extractors?:
      enabled: string[]
      threshold: number         # 0..1 — AI confidence cutoff
```

```mdl
type Calendar
  fields:
    name?: string
    feed: Ref<Feed>             # append-only stream of synced (Google) Events
```

```mdl
type DraftMessage
  fields:
    subject?: string
    to?: string
    body?: string
    replyTo?: Ref<Message>
    mailbox: Ref<Mailbox>       # marker: a Message with properties.mailbox set is a local draft
```

```mdl
# Draft events are the calendar analogue of an email DraftMessage: locally-created Events that
# have not been pushed to Google. They live in the space db (not the calendar feed), are parented to
# their Calendar, and carry no Google foreign key (synced feed Events do). Edited offline, overlaid on
# the calendar, and pushed to Google on save.
type DraftEvent = Event       # an Event with no google.com foreign key, parented to a Calendar
```

```mdl
type Settings
  fields:
    threads?: boolean           # group messages by conversation
```

## Components

```mdl
component MailboxArticle
  desc: Inbox surface for a Mailbox — filterable message list with reading pane.
  props:
    subject: Mailbox
    settings: Settings
  state:
    selected?: Message
    activeFilter?: Filter
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode         # sync / compose / filter actions
  actions:
    selectMessage(message: Message)
    applyFilter(filter: Filter)
    compose()
    reply(message: Message)
    archive(message: Message)
  emits:
    onOpenContact(actor: Actor)
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────┬─────────────────────────┐
    │ [toolbar]    │                         │
    ├──────────────┤                         │
    │ filter chips │  reading pane           │
    │              │                         │
    │ message list │  (selected message      │
    │              │   + related contacts /  │
    │              │   events / threads)     │
    │              │                         │
    └──────────────┴─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component CalendarArticle
  desc: |
    Day/week view of a Calendar. Overlays synced (feed) Events and draft (local) Events on the
    grid and event list. Toolbar (toolbar idiom) offers "Create event" and, when any draft events
    exist, "Save events to calendar" (disabled unless an Integration targets the Calendar). The
    toolbar also slots the connect/sync action (InitializeCalendarAction): "Connect" auth Surface
    when no Integration targets the Calendar, pull-sync button when one does. Selecting an event in
    the list scrolls its date into view on the month grid (CalendarController.scrollTo).
  props:
    subject: Calendar
  state:
    selected?: Event
    selectedDate?: Date          # default date for newly created events
    range: { from: Date; to: Date }
  actions:
    selectEvent(event: Event)    # selects, opens companion, and scrolls the grid to the event date
    createEvent()                # creates a draft Event (db, parented to Calendar) and focuses it
    syncDraft()             # op:syncDraftEvents (spaceId-scoped) for all draft events on this Calendar
    sync()
```

```mdl
component EventArticle
  desc: |
    Event detail (companion to a Calendar). When the event is draft the header is an editable form
    (title · all-day toggle · start · end-or-duration · attendees) and the body is a markdown editor;
    the toolbar shows a Save action (disabled unless an Integration targets the Calendar). The
    attendee list always ends with a blank ActorList row (react-ui-components): typing `@` opens a
    typeahead against Person names/emails; each completed token (an `@<id>` reference or a
    well-formed email) is committed as an attendee. Toolbar (toolbar idiom): Open (promote from
    companion), Create note, Save (draft only), Delete. Editing resolves the live db object
    (useQuery by id) so inputs stay reactive. Operations are invoked with the calendar db's spaceId
    so their space-affinity services (Database/Feed/Credentials) materialize.
  props:
    subject: Event
    companionTo?: Calendar
  state:
    editable: boolean            # true when the event is draft
    allDay: boolean              # whole-day event (date only); maps to Google start.date/end.date
    endMode: explicit | duration # specify an explicit end DateTime or a duration preset (end = start + d)
  actions:
    open()                       # op:layoutOpen — promote from companion to main view
    save()                       # op:syncDraftEvents (spaceId-scoped) for this event
    delete()                     # op:deleteEvent (spaceId-scoped)
    addAttendee(actor: Actor)    # via the blank ActorList row (Person reference or email)
```

```mdl
component EditMessage
  desc: Compose / reply / forward editor for a DraftMessage.
  props:
    draft: DraftMessage
  actions:
    send()
    saveDraft()
    discard()
  emits:
    onSent(message: Message)
```

## Operations

Effectful operations — mutate persistent state or call external services.

```mdl
op addMailbox
  desc: Adds a Mailbox to the active space or collection.
  input:
    object: Mailbox
    target: Database | Collection
  output: string                # DXN of created Mailbox
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op draftEmail
  desc: Creates a new draft email scoped to a mailbox.
  input:
    subject: string
    to: string
    body: string
    mailbox: Ref<Mailbox>
    replyTo?: Ref<Message>
  output: string                # DXN of new draft Message
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op readEmail
  desc: Reads recent messages from a mailbox as a single text payload.
  input:
    mailbox: Ref<Mailbox>
    skip?: number
    limit?: number
  output: string                # rendered message content
  effects: [echo:read, feed:read]
```

```mdl
op classifyEmail
  desc: Picks an appropriate tag for a message from the database's tag set.
  input:
    message: Message
  output: string                # selected tag DXN, or void if none matched
  effects: [echo:read]
  requires: [AiService]
```

```mdl
op googleMailSync
  desc: Pulls messages from Gmail into the mailbox feed.
  input:
    integration: Ref<Integration>
    mailbox?: Ref<Mailbox>      # when omitted, syncs every mailbox on the Integration
    label?: string              # Gmail label (default: inbox)
    after?: number | string     # unix or yyyy-MM-dd
  output: number                # newMessages count
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op googleCalendarSync
  desc: Pulls events from Google Calendar into the calendar feed (stamps a google.com foreign key on each).
  input:
    integration: Ref<Integration>
    calendar?: Ref<Calendar>
    syncBackDays?: number
    syncForwardDays?: number
  output: number                # newEvents count
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op createGoogleCalendarEvent
  desc: Creates a single event on Google Calendar (write counterpart to googleCalendarSync). Requires the calendar.events scope.
  input:
    event: Event
    googleCalendarId: string
    integration: Ref<Integration>
  output: string                # remote Google event id
  effects: [http]
```

```mdl
op syncDraftEvents
  desc: |
    Pushes draft (local, unsynced) events for a Calendar to Google Calendar (the email draft→send
    analogue). For each: createGoogleCalendarEvent, stamp the google.com foreign key, then (after a
    feed re-sync) remove the local draft so the synced feed copy is the source of truth. When `event`
    is given, only that one is synced. NOTE follow-up: re-anchor an event's note relation onto the
    synced copy before deleting the local draft.
  input:
    calendar: Calendar
    event?: Event               # when omitted, syncs all draft events on the Calendar
  output: number                # synced count
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op deleteEvent
  desc: |
    Deletes a calendar event. A draft (local) event is removed from the db; a synced event is
    deleted on Google Calendar by its foreign key and removed from the calendar feed.
  input:
    calendar: Calendar
    event: Event
  output: boolean
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op deleteEmail
  desc: |
    Deletes an email. A draft (local) message is removed from the db; a synced message is moved to the
    Gmail trash by its foreign key (requires gmail.modify scope) and removed from the mailbox feed.
  input:
    mailbox: Mailbox
    message: Message
  output: boolean
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op googleContactsSync
  desc: Pulls contacts from a Google contact group into Person objects.
  input:
    integration: Ref<Integration>
    contactGroupResourceName?: string
  output: number                # upserted count
  effects: [echo:write, http]
```

```mdl
op gmailSend
  desc: Sends a Message via Gmail using integration credentials.
  input:
    message: Message
    integration: Ref<Integration>
  output: string                # remote Gmail thread id
  effects: [http]
```

```mdl
op extractMessage
  desc: Runs configured AI extractors over a message; creates/updates structured objects.
  input:
    message: Message
    extractorId?: string        # specific extractor; default runs all enabled
  output:
    extractorId: string
    created: number
    updated: number
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [AiService]
```

```mdl
op extractContact
  desc: Extracts a Person object from an Actor referenced in a message.
  input:
    actor: Actor
  effects: [echo:write]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Mailbox

  req F-1.1: Mailbox stores messages in an append-only Feed; never mutates past entries.
  req F-1.2: Messages render newest-first with sender, subject, snippet, and timestamp.
  req F-1.3:
    when: settings.threads is true
    then: list groups messages by conversation; shows most recent per thread
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Calendar

  req F-2.1: Calendar stores synced events in an append-only Feed.
  req F-2.2: Day and week views render events ordered by start time.
  req F-2.3: CalendarArticle overlays synced (feed) and draft (local) events together on the grid and list.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Google Sync

  req F-3.1:
    when: user adds a Google Integration with mail scope
    then: op:googleMailSync runs and populates the mailbox feed

  req F-3.2:
    when: user adds a Google Integration with calendar scope
    then: op:googleCalendarSync runs and populates the calendar feed

  req F-3.3:
    when: user adds a Google Integration with contacts scope
    then: op:googleContactsSync upserts Person objects into the space

  req F-3.4: Subsequent syncs use server-side delta tokens; only new/changed records are written.
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Compose & Send

  req F-4.1:
    when: user clicks compose / reply / forward
    then: op:draftEmail creates a DraftMessage; EditMessage opens for editing

  req F-4.2:
    when: user sends a draft
    then: op:gmailSend dispatches via the linked Google Integration
    errors: [SendFailed, NoIntegration]

  req F-4.3:
    when: user clicks delete on a message
    then: op:deleteEmail removes a draft locally, or trashes a synced message on Gmail and drops the feed copy
```

```mdl
feat F-8: Draft Events & Two-way Calendar

  req F-8.1:
    when: user clicks "Create event" on the calendar toolbar
    then: a draft Event is created (db, parented to the Calendar) and focused for editing

  req F-8.2:
    when: an event is draft
    then: EventArticle's header exposes editable title, start/end and body, and the toolbar shows Save

  req F-8.2a:
    when: the user toggles "All day" on a draft
    then: the event is date-only (Event.allDay); it round-trips to Google start.date/end.date (end exclusive)

  req F-8.2b:
    when: the user picks a duration preset instead of an explicit end
    then: endDate = startDate + duration; moving the start preserves the duration

  req F-8.3: User may create multiple draft events offline before saving (e.g. while disconnected).

  req F-8.4:
    when: user clicks Save (per-event in EventArticle, or "Save events to calendar" on the calendar toolbar)
    then: op:syncDraftEvents creates the event(s) on Google Calendar and reconciles into the feed
    errors: [NoIntegration, NoCalendarWriteScope]

  req F-8.5:
    when: user clicks delete on a draft event
    then: op:deleteEvent removes it locally; a synced event is deleted on Google and dropped from the feed
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Filters and Labels

  req F-5.1: User can save a named filter expression on the mailbox.
  req F-5.2:
    when: a saved filter is selected
    then: message list shows only matching messages
```

```mdl
feat F-6: AI Assistance

  req F-6.1: Plugin contributes an Inbox blueprint with read / draft / classify / sync / extract tools.
  req F-6.2:
    when: agent calls op:classifyEmail on a message
    then: best-matching tag is applied; no tag applied below extractors.threshold

  req F-6.3:
    when: agent calls op:extractMessage on a confirmation email
    then: structured objects (e.g. Trip segments) are created or updated
```

```mdl
feat F-7: Related Content

  req F-7.1:
    when: a message is selected
    then: related contacts, events, and thread messages are shown alongside the reading pane

  req F-7.2:
    when: user clicks a related contact
    then: navigation opens the Person object
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Sync Gmail into mailbox
  given: a Mailbox linked to a Google Integration with valid credentials
  when: op:googleMailSync runs
  then:
    - newMessages > 0 on first run
    - Mailbox.feed contains Message entries ordered by received-at
```

```mdl
test T-2: Save and apply filter
  given: Mailbox open with > 1 messages, including one from alice@example.com
  when: user saves filter "from:alice@example.com" and selects it
  then:
    - message list shows only messages matching the filter
```

```mdl
test T-3: Draft and send reply
  given: a Message is selected in the mailbox
  when: user clicks reply, edits the body, and sends
  then:
    - op:draftEmail creates a DraftMessage with replyTo set
    - op:gmailSend dispatches via the linked Integration
    - sent message appears in the mailbox feed on next sync
```

```mdl
test T-4: Classify message
  given: a Message and a tag set with confidence threshold 0.7
  when: op:classifyEmail runs
  then:
    - if best tag confidence ≥ 0.7, tag applied
    - otherwise no tag applied
```

```mdl
test T-5: Extract confirmation
  given: a flight booking confirmation email
  when: op:extractMessage runs with the trip extractor enabled
  then:
    - Trip segment objects created or updated
    - extractMessage output reports created/updated counts
```

```mdl
test T-6: Create and save a draft event
  given: a Calendar linked to a Google Integration with calendar.events scope
  when: user clicks "Create event", edits the title and date, then clicks Save
  then:
    - a draft Event (parented to the Calendar, no google.com foreign key) is created and focused
    - it is overlaid on the calendar grid and event list before saving
    - op:syncDraftEvents calls op:createGoogleCalendarEvent and the event lands in the calendar feed
    - the local draft Event is removed after reconciliation
```

```mdl
test T-7: Delete event and email
  given: a synced Event and a synced Message
  when: user clicks delete in EventArticle and in MessageArticle
  then:
    - op:deleteEvent deletes the event on Google Calendar and removes it from the calendar feed
    - op:deleteEmail trashes the message on Gmail and removes it from the mailbox feed
    - a draft event / draft message would instead be removed locally only
```

